HEADWORD: Isotherombrose
<hw>I*soth`er*om"brose</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Iso-</ets> + Gr. <grk>qe`ros</grk> summer +
<grk>'o`mbros</grk> rain.]</ety> <fld>(Phys. Geog)</fld> <def>A line
connecting or marking points on the earth's surface, which have the same
mean summer rainfall.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Isotonic</ent>⟦br⟧
